label: University of Pennsylvania Ms. Codex 918: Regulae de longis et brevibus syllabis
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Didactic poem outlining the rules of syllabic usage in composition with marginal and interlinear commentary, and an anonymous treatise of prosody.
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: Parchment, iii (modern paper) + 15 + iii (modern paper); 1⁸ 2⁸(-8); [1-15]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.
        Layout: Work 1 written in 18 long lines, with marginal and interlinear annotations; work 2 written in 30 long lines; both works ruled in drypoint; prickings visible.
        Script: Written in an Italian Gothic book script.
        Decoration: Red 1-line and 2-line initials.
        Binding: Modern boards.
        Origin: Written in North Italy, ca. 1200 (Zacour-Hirsch).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn Ms. Codex 918
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 4219225 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/4219225
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/PennManuscripts/html/mscodex918.html
